  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><strong>Bardolino Wine Festival – Italy</strong><br />Date: 29th September – 3rd October 2016 <br />On the shores of <a data-udi="umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473}" title="Lake Garda">Lake Garda</a>, the town of <a data-udi="umb://document/59fcac55a66d4666ae4b0cca449364d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/59fcac55a66d4666ae4b0cca449364d1}" title="Bardolino">Bardolino</a> brings the summer season to a close, with a celebration of the new harvest of the grapes during the annual Bardolino Wine Festival. As well as wine tasting, there will be food stalls offering delicious local specialities, live music and a spectacular fireworks display over the lake. Tours are also available around the area's vineyards and wineries. Inghams offers 7 nights half-board accommodation staying at the <a data-udi="umb://document/f3d701a9e80e4dc8859bbab4327b06ff" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f3d701a9e80e4dc8859bbab4327b06ff}" title="Aida Hotel">3* Aida Hotel</a>, Bardolino, from £659 per person, departing 24 September 2016, including return flights and transfers. For more information or to book visit <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays">www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays</a> or call 01483 791 116.</p>
<p><strong>Wildschönau Almabtrieb Festival - Austria</strong><br />Date: 17th September 2016<br />During September the alpine villages of<a data-udi="umb://document/c9325d9a77054a3c8190f3ab0da21760" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c9325d9a77054a3c8190f3ab0da21760}" title="Austria"> Austria </a>celebrate the annual ‘Almabrieb’. This wonderful traditional festival literally means ‘ driving down the mountain’ and celebrates the end of the summer, when the sound of cowbells echo through the valley as hundreds of cows are led down the mountain, decorated in traditional costumes and led to their stables for the winter – it’s quite a spectacular sight! Alongside the "Cow Train" procession are village fetes and celebrations throughout the mountains.<br />Inghams offers 7 nights half-board accommodation staying at the <a data-udi="umb://document/33cf44909b324ad3a5d306982645d5e5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/33cf44909b324ad3a5d306982645d5e5}" title="Hotel Austria">3* Hotel Austria</a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/b4b80bb5361b479c9ffa0028dc2843c4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b4b80bb5361b479c9ffa0028dc2843c4}" title="Niederau">Niderau</a> from £599 per person, departing 14 September 2016, including return flights and transfers. For more information or to book visit <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays">www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays</a> or call 01483 791 116.</p>
<p><strong>Knödelfest (Dumpling Festival) – St Johann, Austria</strong> <br />Date: 24th September 2016<br />St Johann’s Knödelfest (Dumpling Festival) celebrates one of Austria’s most popular dishes. Get ready for the largest display of dumplings the world has ever seen – 25,000 dumplings in 23 different varieties from traditional to modern, from sweet to savoury are presented on a 300m long table! Join in the festivities with live music late into the night. Inghams offers 7 nights at the <a data-udi="umb://document/300e94b0bab949948bf35b806de8d57b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/300e94b0bab949948bf35b806de8d57b}" title="Q Hotel Maria Theresia">4* Hotel Maria Theresia</a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/0424394c50b54ef4848722ee185d0739" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0424394c50b54ef4848722ee185d0739}" title="Kitzbuhel">Kitzbuhel</a>, from £499 per person, departing 17 September, including return flights and transfers. For more information or to book visit <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays">www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays</a> or call 01483 791 116.</p>
<p><strong>Traditional Handcraft Festival – Austria</strong> <br />Date: 10th – 11th September 2016<br />Take a step back in time in <a data-udi="umb://document/a71713291d5d4220aea1b806f34cd053" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a71713291d5d4220aea1b806f34cd053}" title="Seefeld">Seefeld</a> where you can marvel at old handicrafts, as the old masters come together to celebrate their workmanship. With more than 100 stands and exhibitions, from basket weavers to barrel makers they will be demonstrating their skills during the festival, with plenty of traditional music, food and drink. Inghams offers 7 nights half-board accommodation staying at the <a data-udi="umb://document/a07831d24602497faebe4601e89426b4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a07831d24602497faebe4601e89426b4}" title="Hotel Alpina">4* Hotel Alpina</a> from £549 per person, departing 10 September 2016, including return flights and transfers. For more information or to book visit <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays">www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays</a> or call 01483 791 116.</p>
<p><strong>Fairy-tale Nights Festival – Italy</strong><br />Date: 25th August – 28th August 2016<br />Families heading to the lakeside resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01}" title="Riva">Riva de Garda</a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904}" title="Italy">Italy </a>this August will be transformed into the magical world of Aladdin during its annual Fairy Tale Nights festival. Riva’s streets and squares will tell the story of Alladin through live music, street performances, acrobats and jugglers, ending with a spectacular fireworks display over the lake. Inghams offers 7 nights, half-board accommodation at the <a data-udi="umb://document/5cdbdffcbd3f413496166a1214d6740d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5cdbdffcbd3f413496166a1214d6740d}" title="Villa Nicolli Hotel">4* Hotel Villa Nicolli</a>, Riva from £549 per person, departing 24 August 2016, including return flights and transfers. For more information or to book visit <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays">www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays</a> or call 01483 791 116.</p>
